<chapter id="prop-ntservice-console">
    <title>wrapper.ntservice.console Property</title>
    <section>
        <title>Configuration Property Overview</title>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <ulink url="properties.html">Configuration Property Overview</ulink>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <ulink url="props-nt.html">Windows NT/2000/XP Configuration Properties</ulink>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <ulink url="properties.html#name">Property List by Name</ulink>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>wrapper.ntservice.console</title>
        <para>
            Setting this property will cause the Wrapper to allocate and display a
            console window when running as an NT service.  The console will only be
            visible if the
            <ulink url="prop-ntservice-interactive.html">wrapper.ntservice.interactive</ulink>
            property is also set to true.  Defaults to false.
        </para>
        <informalexample>
            <simpara><emphasis>Example:</emphasis></simpara>
            <screen format="linespecific"><![CDATA[wrapper.ntservice.console=true]]></screen>
        </informalexample>
        <note>
            <para>
                <ulink url="prop-restart-reload-configuration.html">Reloading</ulink>
                the Wrapper configuration will have no effect on the value of this property.
                Changes will not take effect until the Wrapper has been restarted.
            </para>
        </note>
    </section>
</chapter>
